author: snichol
msg: Provide a more complete list of SOAP 1.1 features not implemented and
reference the spec section for each item.

author: snichol
msg: Avoid use of ws2mbs macro when handling strings.  That macro makes a copy
of the string on the stack, which is a problem for long strings.

author: snichol
msg: Have TcpTunnel dump to System.out, which means default character encoding
will be used to translate bytes sent over the wire.  (TcpTunnelGui
always uses iso-8859-1, which is not always appropriate, either.)

author: snichol
msg: Test handling of nulls for various data types.  Improve text for faults
thrown when nulls of primitive types cannot be handled.

author: snichol
msg: Register DOMFaultHandler for the ServiceManager to provide clients
with a stack trace on faults.
